But the town has finally put in a bus service so I am hoping my exercise will be back to what I used to allways do. No gym time!

When my tent mate here in Africa, Shelley passed away we all put money towards a gift for her husband and children. We had a lovely afternoon swimming while Shelley's husband's Aunt and two Uncle's watched the children.To date we had only been in the country a couple of days and we already met upp to take in one of Uganda's little festivals.After that I was invited back to the Oil Sunday School by Hanna for pysical therapy for both Shelley's husband and I. Shelley helped get us started in a program that we could maintain without her, and we were both doing really well. But since she passed we have both slid backwards a bit and needed to get back on track.After that I went to a basketball game that the Canadian nurses have set up with the Ugandan Nurses. The pick up game consisted of maybe 8 Ugandans including the Chinese nurse, 3 Indian nurses from Kolkata (who were superb athletes) and Rogers and I.
